This paper discusses the robustness of face recognition algorithms, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the effect of bias on face recognition models, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of GANs for morphing/tampering, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV and cs.CR, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.MM.
